&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a motivated Cybersecurity SOC Analyst Intern to join our Security Operations Center. This role provides hands-on experience in monitoring, detecting, and responding to security events. The intern will work alongside experienced analysts to help protect organizational systems and data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor security alerts and events in SIEM and endpoint detection tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in triaging and investigating security alerts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document findings and escalate incidents when appropriate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support analysis of phishing emails and suspicious activity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help review logs from systems, networks, and applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in incident response activities and post-incident reviews&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with threat intelligence research and enrichment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow security procedures and contribute to process improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently pursuing or recently completed a degree in Cybersecurity, Information Technology, Computer Science, or related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of cybersecurity concepts (e.g., phishing, malware, network attacks)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with operating systems (Windows, Linux)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Eagerness to learn in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred (Nice to Have)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to SIEM tools (e.g., Splunk, Rapid7 InsightIDR, Elastic)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with EDR tools (e.g., SentinelOne, CrowdStrike)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of networking (TCP/IP, DNS, HTTP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of common frameworks (MITRE ATT&amp;amp;CK, NIST)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with scripting (Python, PowerShell)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Gain&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Real-world SOC experience monitoring and responding to threats&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentorship from experienced cybersecurity analysts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to enterprise security tools and workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of incident response lifecycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to contribute to active security operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary Range:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;collapsed-field-text&quot;&gt;$18.80 - $25.43 &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary is commensurate to experience, location, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
